<title type="html"><![CDATA[Do UxROM games write to CHR-RAM after initializing?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6626&amp;p=64542#p64542"><![CDATA[
Yeah, most CHR-RAM games update CHR-RAM quite frequently. They do it <strong>at least</strong> between levels and such, but usually more often than that.<br /><br />Open some games in FCEUX and open the PPU viewer. There you can see the current state of the pattern tables, and it's usually easy to see when tiles are being rewritten.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Tue Jul 20, 2010 6:49 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
